      "raw_text": "clared to contain the mildest kind\nof articles.\n\n\nJames Wilson, now in the coun-\nty Jail for criminal conspiracy, was\nthe managing editor of the Indus\ntrial Worker until he was captured\nin the dragnet laid by the police for\nthe agitators and members Of the\nrevolutionary forces. e. J. Foote\nthen came from Portland to edit\nthe paper, but almost before his\nquill work in Spokane began, he,\ntoo, was landed behind the bars of\nthe city Jail on a criminal conspir-\nacy charge. A. e. Cousins, assist\nant to Editor Wilson, soon, follow\ned, and since then considerable Sc\ncrecy has enshrouded the editorial\nend of the paper."
